{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870910586,"sessionID":"ses_285d896f9ffekS1IV9gosr9Bi7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a279c41001swJ5G2LTY9AOd5","messageID":"msg_d7a278753001tafcWB7r1DTyZ7","sessionID":"ses_285d896f9ffekS1IV9gosr9Bi7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7cc95ea53aae4342bcc151d52f833092","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: DockerService Enhancements (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Add `get_image_info()` method to `DockerService`\n20:   - Extract image_id, image_size, and format size to human-readable string\n21:   - Signature: `get_image_info(image_name: str, tag: str) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n22:   - Return: `{\"image_id\": str, \"image_size\": str}`\n23:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n24:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_get_image_info -v`\n25: \n26: - [ ] **T1.2**: Add `_format_size()` helper method to `DockerService`\n27:   - Convert bytes to human-readable format (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n28:   - Handle KB, MB, GB ranges\n29:   - Private method used by `get_image_info()`\n30:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n31:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_format_size -v`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.3**: Update `build_image()` method signature and return structure\n34:   - Add `dockerfile_path` parameter (separate from context_path)\n35:   - Add `build_args` parameter for proxy support\n36:   - Return `{\"image_name\": str, \"image_id\": str, \"image_size\": str, \"build_time\": float, \"tag\": str}`\n37:   - Stream build logs when `verbose=True`\n38:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n39:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_build_image_with_proxy -v`\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T1.4**: Add `check_docker_available()` method improvements\n42:   - Return `True/False` boolean (already exists, verify correctness)\n43:   - Log Docker daemon status in verbose mode\n44:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n45:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_check_docker_available -v`\n46: \n47: ### Phase 2: BuildRuntime Class (ST-2)\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `BuildRuntime` class skeleton in `build_runtime.py`\n50:   - Import dependencies: `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n51:   - Import services: `MetadataService`, `DockerService`\n52:   - Define constructor: `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n53:   - Initialize `self.verbose`, `self._metadata_service`, `self._docker_service`\n54:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n55:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\"`\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `build()` main entry method\n58:   - Signature: `build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n59:   - Load metadata via `self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n60:   - Store `original_version = metadata.version` for rollback\n61:   - Call `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)`\n62:   - Call `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` вҶ’ returns `new_tag`\n63:   - Call `_build_local()` or `_build_cloud()` based on `metadata.build_mode`\n64:   - Call `_update_build_metadata()` on success\n65:   - Rollback version on failure, raise `RuntimeError`\n66:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n67:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_local_success -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_validate_build_prerequisites()` method\n70:   - Check `self._docker_service.check_docker_available()` вҶ’ raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available\")`\n71:   - Check `workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"` exists вҶ’ raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found\")`\n72:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n73:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_docker_unavailable -v`\n74: \n75: ### Phase 3: Version Increment Logic (ST-3)\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `_increment_version()` method\n78:   - Import `semver` library\n79:   - Handle valid semver `X.Y.Z` вҶ’ bump_patch вҶ’ `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n80:   - Handle `v`-prefixed non-semver `vX.Y` вҶ’ append `.1` вҶ’ `vX.Y.1`\n81:   - Handle non-semver string вҶ’ append `-1` вҶ’ `custom-1`\n82:   - Handle `None/empty` вҶ’ return `\"latest\"`\n83:   - Save updated `metadata.version` via `self._metadata_service.save_metadata()`\n84:   - Return new tag string\n85:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_increment_semver -v`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Add version rollback logic in `build()` method\n89:   - Store `original_version` before increment\n90:   - On exception in build: `metadata.version = original_version`\n91:   - Call `self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)`\n92:   - Raise `RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}. Version rolled back to {original_version}\")`\n93:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_rollback_on_failure -v`\n95: \n96: ### Phase 4: Build Execution Methods (ST-4)\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `_build_local()` method\n99:   - Resolve image_name: `metadata.agent_name`\n100:   - Build args: `{\"PROXY\": options.get(\"proxy\")}` if proxy provided\n101:   - Call `self._docker_service.build_image()` with:\n102:     - `dockerfile_path=workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"`\n103:     - `context_path=workspace_path`\n104:     - `image_name=metadata.agent_name`\n105:     - `tag=new_tag`\n106:     - `build_args=build_args`\n107:   - Return build result dict\n108:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n109:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_local_success -v`\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement `_build_cloud()` placeholder method\n112:   - Check `metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n113:   - Return placeholder dict: `{\"image_name\": metadata.agent_name, \"image_id\": \"cloud-placeholder\", \"image_size\": \"0 MB\", \"build_time\": 0, \"tag\": \"latest\"}`\n114:   - Log warning: `\"Cloud build not implemented\"`\n115:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n116:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_cloud_placeholder -v`\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `_update_build_metadata()` method\n119:   - Update `metadata.image` dict with:\n120:     - `\"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"]`\n121:     - `\"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"]`\n122:     - `\"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"]`\n123:     - `\"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"]`\n124:     - `\"tag\": tag`\n125:   - Call `self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)`\n126:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n127:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_update_build_metadata -v`\n128: \n129: ### Phase 5: CLI Command Implementation (ST-5)\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T5.1**: Add `build` command to `main.py`\n132:   - Import `BuildRuntime` from `agentcube.runtime.build_runtime`\n133:   - Define Typer command with options:\n134:     - `workspace: str = \".\"` (alias `-f`, `--workspace`)\n135:     - `proxy: Optional[str] = None` (alias `-p`, `--proxy`)\n136:     - `cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None` (`--cloud-provider`)\n137:     - `output: Optional[str] = None` (`--output`)\n138:     - `verbose: bool = False` (`--verbose`)\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n140:   - Verification: `kubectl-agentcube build --help`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `build` command handler\n143:   - Resolve workspace path: `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n144:   - Initialize `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)`\n145:   - Use Rich Progress spinner: `progress.add_task(\"Building agent image...\", total=None)`\n146:   - Call `runtime.build(workspace_path, proxy=proxy, cloud_provider=cloud_provider, output=output)`\n147:   - Print success output with Rich formatting:\n148:     - `[green]Build completed successfully[/green]`\n149:     - `Image: {image_name}:{tag}`\n150:     - `Image ID: {image_id}`\n151:     - `Size: {image_size}`\n152:     - `Build time: {build_time}s`\n153:   - Handle errors via `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)`\n154:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n155:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_cli.py -v` (update test)\n156: \n157: ### Phase 6: Unit Tests - BuildRuntime (ST-6)\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create test file `test_build_runtime.py`\n160:   - Import `pytest`, `unittest.mock`, `Path`\n161:   - Import `BuildRuntime`, `AgentMetadata`\n162:   - Create fixtures: `mock_docker_service`, `mock_metadata_service`, `tmp_workspace`\n163:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n164:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v`\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T6.2**: Test `build_local_success`\n167:   - Mock DockerService to return valid build result\n168:   - Mock MetadataService to load/save metadata\n169:   - Verify build returns correct result dict\n170:   - Verify metadata.version incremented\n171:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n172:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_local_success -v`\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T6.3**: Test `build_docker_unavailable`\n175:   - Mock `check_docker_available()` to return `False`\n176:   - Expect `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n177:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n178:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_docker_unavailable -v`\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T6.4**: Test `build_missing_dockerfile`\n181:   - Create tmp workspace without Dockerfile\n182:   - Expect `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")`\n183:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n184:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_missing_dockerfile -v`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T6.5**: Test version increment scenarios\n187:   - Test semver: `1.2.3` вҶ’ `1.2.4`\n188:   - Test v-prefix semver: `v1.2.3` вҶ’ `v1.2.4`\n189:   - Test v-prefix non-semver: `v1.0` вҶ’ `v1.0.1`\n190:   - Test non-semver: `custom` вҶ’ `custom-1`\n191:   - Test empty: `None` вҶ’ `\"latest\"`\n192:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n193:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_increment -v`\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T6.6**: Test version rollback on failure\n196:   - Mock `build_image()` to raise `BuildError`\n197:   - Verify metadata.version restored to original\n198:   - Verify `RuntimeError` raised with rollback message\n199:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n200:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_version_rollback_on_failure -v`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T6.7**: Test `build_cloud_placeholder`\n203:   - Set `metadata.build_mode = \"cloud\"`\n204:   - Verify placeholder dict returned\n205:   - Verify warning logged\n206:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n207:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::TestBuildRuntime::test_build_cloud_placeholder -v`\n208: \n209: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests - DockerService (ST-7)\n210: \n211: - [ ] **T7.1**: Create/update `test_docker_service.py`\n212:   - Test `check_docker_available()` with mocked Docker client\n213:   - Test `build_image()` with mocked `client.images.build()`\n214:   - Test `get_image_info()` with mocked image object\n215:   - Test `_format_size()` helper method\n216:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n217:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v`\n218: \n219: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test `build_image_with_proxy`\n220:   - Mock Docker build API\n221:   - Pass `build_args={\"PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"}`\n222:   - Verify buildargs passed to Docker API\n223:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n224:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_build_image_with_proxy -v`\n225: \n226: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test `get_image_info`\n227:   - Mock image with `id=\"sha256:abc123\"` and `attrs[\"Size\"]=125300000`\n228:   - Verify returns `{\"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123\", \"image_size\": \"125.3 MB\"}`\n229:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n230:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_get_image_info -v`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test `_format_size` helper\n233:   - Test bytes: `500` вҶ’ `\"500 B\"`\n234:   - Test KB: `1024` вҶ’ `\"1.0 KB\"`\n235:   - Test MB: `1048576` вҶ’ `\"1.0 MB\"`\n236:   - Test GB: `1073741824` вҶ’ `\"1.0 GB\"`\n237:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n238:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService::test_format_size -v`\n239: \n240: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests (ST-8)\n241: \n242: - [ ] **T8.1**: Create integration test `test_build_integration.py`\n243:   - Test full workflow: validate вҶ’ increment вҶ’ build вҶ’ update metadata\n244:   - Use tmp workspace with Dockerfile and agent_metadata.yaml\n245:   - Mock Docker SDK for build execution\n246:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n247:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py -v`\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T8.2**: Test `build_after_pack` integration\n250:   - Pack creates Dockerfile, build succeeds\n251:   - Verify metadata.image updated correctly\n252:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n253:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py::TestBuildIntegration::test_build_after_pack -v`\n254: \n255: - [ ] **T8.3**: Test `rebuild_increments_version` integration\n256:   - First build: `version=\"v1.0\"` вҶ’ `tag=\"v1.0.1\"`\n257:   - Second build: `version=\"v1.0.1\"` вҶ’ `tag=\"v1.0.2\"`\n258:   - Verify version increments on each build\n259:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py`\n260:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py::TestBuildIntegration::test_rebuild_increments_version -v`\n261: \n262: ### Phase 9: Dependencies & Validation (ST-9)\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T9.1**: Add `semver` dependency to `pyproject.toml`\n265:   - Version: `semver>=3.0.0`\n266:   - Purpose: Semantic version parsing and bumping\n267:   - File: `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n268:   - Verification: `pip install semver && python -c \"import semver\"`\n269: \n270: - [ ] **T9.2**: Update `runtime/__init__.py` exports\n271:   - Add `BuildRuntime` to exports\n272:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n273:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime import BuildRuntime\"`\n274: \n275: - [ ] **T9.3**: Run all tests with coverage\n276:   - `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing`\n277:   - Coverage target: >80% for `build_runtime.py`\n278:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/`\n279:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --cov=agentcube`\n280: \n281: - [ ] **T9.4**: Run lint and type check\n282:   - `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n283:   - `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n284:   - Fix any lint/type errors\n285:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n286:   - Verification: `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/ && mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/`\n287: \n288: ---\n289: \n290: ## Task Dependencies\n291: \n292: ```\n293: T1.1 вҶ’ T1.2 вҶ’ T1.3 вҶ’ T1.4\n294:            вҶ“\n295:         T2.1 вҶ’ T2.2 вҶ’ T2.3\n296:                вҶ“\n297:         T3.1 вҶ’ T3.2\n298:                вҶ“\n299:         T4.1 вҶ’ T4.2 вҶ’ T4.3\n300:                вҶ“\n301:         T5.1 вҶ’ T5.2\n302:                вҶ“\n303:         T6.1 вҶ’ T6.2 вҶ’ T6.3 вҶ’ T6.4 вҶ’ T6.5 вҶ’ T6.6 вҶ’ T6.7\n304:                вҶ“\n305:         T7.1 вҶ’ T7.2 вҶ’ T7.3 вҶ’ T7.4\n306:                вҶ“\n307:         T8.1 вҶ’ T8.2 вҶ’ T8.3\n308:                вҶ“\n309:         T9.1 вҶ’ T9.2 вҶ’ T9.3 вҶ’ T9.4\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Verification Commands\n315: \n316: | Task | Verification Command |\n317: |------|----------------------|\n318: | DockerService tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n319: | BuildRuntime tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py -v` |\n320: | Integration tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py -v` |\n321: | All tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v` |\n322: | Coverage | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` |\n323: | Build command help | `kubectl-agentcube build --help` |\n324: | Lint check | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n325: | Type check | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n326: | Import test | `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\"` |\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Acceptance Criteria\n331: \n332: - [ ] `BuildRuntime` class defined with `__init__`, `build`, `_validate_build_prerequisites`\n333: - [ ] `_increment_version()` handles semver, v-prefix, non-semver, None cases\n334: - [ ] `_build_local()` calls DockerService with correct parameters\n335: - [ ] `_build_cloud()` returns placeholder for cloud mode\n336: - [ ] `_update_build_metadata()` updates `metadata.image` dict\n337: - [ ] Version rollback on build failure\n338: - [ ] `build` Typer command with all options: `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n339: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner during build\n340: - [ ] Success output: image name, ID, size, build time\n341: - [ ] Error handling via `_handle_error()`\n342: - [ ] DockerService `get_image_info()` method\n343: - [ ] DockerService `_format_size()` helper\n344: - [ ] DockerService `build_image()` with `build_args` support\n345: - [ ] Unit tests for version increment scenarios\n346: - [ ] Unit tests for rollback logic\n347: - [ ] Unit tests for Docker unavailable/missing Dockerfile\n348: - [ ] Integration tests for build workflow\n349: - [ ] Integration test for packвҶ’build workflow\n350: - [ ] Integration test for rebuild version increment\n351: - [ ] `semver>=3.0.0` dependency added\n352: - [ ] `BuildRuntime` exported from `runtime/__init__.py`\n353: - [ ] All tests pass with >80% coverage\n354: - [ ] Ruff lint passes\n355: - [ ] MyPy type check passes\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## File Changes Summary\n360: \n361: | File | Action | Lines Changed | Description |\n362: |------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n363: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Create | ~120 | `BuildRuntime` class with build orchestration |\n364: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Modify | ~5 | Export `BuildRuntime` |\n365: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | ~30 | Add `get_image_info`, `_format_size`, update `build_image` |\n366: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modify | ~40 | Add `build` command with Typer options |\n367: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py` | Create | ~200 | Unit tests for BuildRuntime |\n368: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py` | Modify | ~50 | Unit tests for new DockerService methods |\n369: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_integration.py` | Create | ~80 | Integration tests for build workflow |\n370: | `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` | Modify | ~2 | Add `semver>=3.0.0` dependency |\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ## Implementation Notes\n375: \n376: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n377: - **Reference implementation**: `PackRuntime` in `pack_runtime.py` provides similar pattern\n378: - **DockerService already exists** with `check_docker_available` and `build_image` - enhance these\n379: - **semver library**: Use `semver.VersionInfo.parse()` and `bump_patch()` for version increment\n380: - **Version increment strategy**:\n381:   - Valid semver `X.Y.Z`: bump_patch вҶ’ `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n382:   - v-prefixed semver `vX.Y.Z`: preserve prefix вҶ’ `vX.Y.(Z+1)`\n383:   - v-prefixed non-semver `vX.Y`: append `.1` вҶ’ `vX.Y.1`\n384:   - Non-semver string: append `-1` вҶ’ `string-1`\n385:   - None/empty: use `\"latest\"`\n386: - **Proxy support**: Pass as `build_args={\"PROXY\": proxy_url}` to Docker SDK\n387: - **Rollback pattern**: Store original version, restore on exception\n388: - **Rich Progress**: Use `SpinnerColumn` + `TextColumn` for build spinner\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Implementation Timeline\n393: \n394: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n395: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n396: | Phase 1: DockerService Enhancements | T1.1, T1.2, T1.3, T1.4 | Pending | 0% |\n397: | Phase 2: BuildRuntime Class | T2.1, T2.2, T2.3 | Pending | 0% |\n398: | Phase 3: Version Increment Logic | T3.1, T3.2 | Pending | 0% |\n399: | Phase 4: Build Execution Methods | T4.1, T4.2, T4.3 | Pending | 0% |\n400: | Phase 5: CLI Command Implementation | T5.1, T5.2 | Pending | 0% |\n401: | Phase 6: Unit Tests - BuildRuntime | T6.1-T6.7 | Pending | 0% |\n402: | Phase 7: Unit Tests - DockerService | T7.1-T7.4 | Pending | 0% |\n403: | Phase 8: Integration Tests | T8.1-T8.3 | Pending | 0% |\n404: | Phase 9: Dependencies & Validation | T9.1-T9.4 | Pending | 0% |\n405: \n406: **Total Progress: 0% Complete (0/29 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 406 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: DockerService Enhancements (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Add `get_image_info()` method to `DockerService`\n  - Extract image_id, image_size, and format size to human-readable string","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775870910566,"end":1775870910584}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870910589,"sessionID":"ses_285d896f9ffekS1IV9gosr9Bi7","part":{"id":"prt_d7a27a0080019QAYwPLLK4cKqa","messageID":"msg_d7a278753001tafcWB7r1DTyZ7","sessionID":"ses_285d896f9ffekS1IV9gosr9Bi7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c1725e66b6814182911a81efe69be55f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө\n2: \n3: ## жҰӮиҝ°\n4: \n5: | еұһжҖ§ | еҖј |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-021 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (зӣ®зҡ„)\n15: \n16: Implement the `build` command in AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces. The command orchestrates the entire build lifecycle: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK or cloud provider, and updating metadata with build results.\n17: \n18: **Current State**: CLI has `pack` command that generates Dockerfile and packages workspace, but no build capability. Users must manually run `docker build` after packaging.\n19: \n20: **Target State**: \n21: - Single `kubectl-agentcube build` command that builds container image from packaged workspace\n22: - Automatic version increment (patch bump) before build with rollback on failure\n23: - Support for local Docker build mode (cloud mode placeholder)\n24: - Metadata updated with image info, build time, and image ID\n25: - Proxy support for dependency resolution\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (иҢғеӣҙ)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` class with build orchestration logic |\n36: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `build` Typer command with CLI options |\n37: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration (build, push, remove) |\n38: \n39: ### 2.2 BuildRuntime Methods\n40: \n41: | Method | Purpose |\n42: |--------|---------|\n43: | `build(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n44: | `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` | Patch bump version (X.Y.Z вҶ’ X.Y.Z+1) or append .1 |\n45: | `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)` | Check Docker availability, Dockerfile existence |\n46: | `_build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Local Docker build via SDK |\n47: | `_build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Cloud build (placeholder for future) |\n48: | `_update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, build_result, tag)` | Persist image info to metadata YAML |\n49: \n50: ### 2.3 CLI Options\n51: \n52: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n53: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n54: | `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n55: | `--proxy` / `-p` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n56: | `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n57: | `--output` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for build artifacts |\n58: | `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n59: \n60: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n61: \n62: | Item | Reason |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Cloud build implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n65: | Multi-architecture builds | Not specified in requirements; future enhancement |\n66: | Build cache optimization | Docker SDK handles caching internally |\n67: | Image vulnerability scanning | Separate security concern |\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## 3. Impact Analysis (еҪұе“ҚеҲҶжһҗ)\n72: \n73: ### 3.1 ж–°еўһж–Үд»¶\n74: \n75: ```\n76: cmd/cli/\n77: в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentcube/\n78: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ runtime/\n79: в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ build_runtime.py      # BuildRuntime class\n80: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ services/\n81: в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ docker_service.py     # DockerService class\n82: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ cli/\n83: в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.py               # build command (addition to existing)\n84: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ models/\n85: в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ pack_models.py        # MetadataOptions (shared with pack)\n86: в””в”Җв”Җ tests/\n87:     в””в”Җв”Җ test_build_runtime.py     # Unit tests for BuildRuntime\n88:     в””в”Җв”Җ test_docker_service.py    # Unit tests for DockerService\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n92: \n93: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n94: |------------|---------|--------|\n95: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; required for local build |\n96: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n97: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and status output |\n98: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n99: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Version bump logic |\n100: \n101: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n102: \n103: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n104: |----------|--------------|\n105: | `publish` command | Uses built image name/tag from metadata |\n106: | `status` command | Reads image info from metadata |\n107: | `pack` command | Provides Dockerfile path for build |\n108: | Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent` |\n109: \n110: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n111: \n112: - **Metadata schema**: Adding `image` field with sub-fields (`image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`, `tag`) to `AgentMetadata`\n113: - **Version field**: Build modifies `metadata.version` in-place; concurrent builds could conflict\n114: - **Dockerfile location**: Build expects `Dockerfile` at workspace root (generated by `pack`)\n115: \n116: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n117: \n118: - Docker SDK `docker.from_env()` requires Docker daemon running\n119: - Version increment follows semver pattern: `X.Y.Z` вҶ’ `X.Y.(Z+1)`\n120: - Non-semver versions: append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0` вҶ’ `v1.0.1`)\n121: - Empty version: fallback to `{version}-1` or generate timestamp-based tag\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (еӨҮйҖүж–№жЎҲ)\n126: \n127: ### Alternative 1: Shell Command Execution\n128: \n129: **Approach**: Execute `docker build` via `subprocess.run()` instead of Docker SDK.\n130: \n131: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n132: |--------|------------|\n133: | Pros | Simpler implementation; no SDK dependency |\n134: | Cons | No structured output parsing; harder error handling; no image info extraction; platform-specific quirks |\n135: \n136: **Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK provides structured image info (image_id, size) and cleaner exception handling.\n137: \n138: ### Alternative 2: Kaniko for Rootless Builds\n139: \n140: **Approach**: Use Kaniko executor for builds without Docker daemon.\n141: \n142: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n143: |--------|------------|\n144: | Pros | No Docker daemon required; CI-friendly; rootless |\n145: | Cons | Additional dependency; requires Kubernetes environment; not suitable for local dev workflow |\n146: \n147: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as optional build backend for cloud mode.\n148: \n149: ### Alternative 3: Buildah/Podman\n150: \n151: **Approach**: Support Buildah or Podman as alternative container build tools.\n152: \n153: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n154: |--------|------------|\n155: | Pros | Daemonless; OCI-compliant; rootless option |\n156: | Cons | Different CLI interface; less Python SDK support; broader compatibility testing needed |\n157: \n158: **Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK covers primary use case; Podman support could be future extension.\n159: \n160: ### Alternative 4: Manual Version Management\n161: \n162: **Approach**: Require user to specify version via `--version` flag instead of auto-increment.\n163: \n164: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n165: |--------|------------|\n166: | Pros | Explicit control; no rollback complexity |\n167: | Cons | Manual burden; potential duplicate tags; workflow friction |\n168: \n169: **Decision**: Rejected. Auto-increment with rollback on failure provides safer workflow per spec requirements.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 5. Risks\n174: \n175: | Risk | Mitigation |\n176: |------|------------|\n177: | Docker daemon unavailable | `_validate_build_prerequisites` checks `DockerService.check_docker_available()` before build |\n178: | Version rollback race condition | Build modifies metadata file; use atomic write pattern |\n179: | Build timeout on large images | Docker SDK streaming build; no explicit timeout in spec |\n180: | Registry auth for push (future) | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles auth when credentials provided |\n181: | Image name collision | Use `{agent_name}:{version}` pattern; sanitize agent_name |\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n186: \n187: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.check_docker_available()` with `docker.from_env()` try/catch\n188: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.build_image()` with streaming logs, build_args for proxy\n189: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.get_image_info()` for image_id, size extraction\n190: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.push_image()` with optional registry auth\n191: - [ ] Implement `DockerService.remove_image()` with graceful failure handling\n192: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` with semver logic\n193: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` for Docker + Dockerfile check\n194: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._build_local()` orchestrating Docker build\n195: - [ ] Implement `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()` persisting results\n196: - [ ] Add `build` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n197: - [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n198: - [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for build status\n199: - [ ] Add `image` field to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n200: - [ ] Unit tests for version increment edge cases\n201: - [ ] Unit tests for Docker unavailable scenarios\n202: - [ ] Integration test for full build workflow\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## 7. References\n207: \n208: - Spec: `changes/AR-021/spec.md`\n209: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n210: - CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` вҖ” Requirement: `build` command\n211: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n212: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n213: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 213 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 вҖ” CLI build е‘Ҫд»Ө\n\n## жҰӮиҝ°\n\n| еұһжҖ§ | еҖј |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-021 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (зӣ®зҡ„)\n\nImplement the `build` command in AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces. The command orchestrates the entire build lifecycle: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK or cloud provider, and updating metadata with build results.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` command that generates Dockerfile and packages workspace, but no build capability. Users must manually run `docker build` after packaging.\n\n**Target State**: ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870910569,"end":1775870910587}}}}
